    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-20T00:00:00-05:00"
                n="[Unnumbered document following Document 710 (#46)]" subtype="historical-document"
                type="document" xml:id="d710a-46">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_TSH1">Truman</persName> Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the President</hi>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d710a-46fn2">This brief memorandum is a manuscript notation
                        by <persName corresp="#p_TSH1">Truman</persName> on the <persName
                            corresp="#p_LFAWD1">Leahy</persName> memorandum quoted in footnote 1 to
                            <ref target="#d1275">document No. 1275</ref>, <hi rend="italic"
                            >post</hi>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-20">Undated</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Question<note n="3" xml:id="d710a-46fn3">i. e., when the Soviet Chiefs of Staff
                        would meet with the United States Chiefs of Staff.</note> asked of <persName
                        corresp="#p_SGIV1">Stalin</persName> after meeting on 20th. Had already
                    asked him when he called.<note n="4" xml:id="d710a-46fn4">See <hi rend="italic"
                            >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_44">p. 44</ref>.</note> Agreed to it in a
                    few days.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
